SAPI (Small Arms Protection Inserts) Plates or Ceramic plates (also known as trauma plates) are commonly used as inserts for soft body armour. Most SAPI plates used in the body armor industry can protect against a NIJ level III and IV with a IIIA vest supporting. SAPI plates are a form of composite armour. Insert plates may also be manufactured from steel.

The standard SAPI plate is made of 98% aluminum oxide (alumina), which is then bonded into aramid fiber. These plates are often worn by army personnel needing protection from heavy rifle fire. All XM193 product is the same regardless of the sku or part number. (ie. XM193C is the same as XM193BK, XM193F and etc…) The only difference is the package configuration. This configuration includes 420 rounds in bulk packaging or 840 rounds in milspec can. *See pricing below.

CASE: Brass (Copper Alloy No. 260)

PRIMER: M41 Operating Range: (-40 degrees to +125 degrees F)
PRIMER SEALANT: Water resistant lacquer
CASE MOUTH SEALANT: Yes
CASE KNURL: No
HEADSTAMP: Each loaded cartridge shall be headstamped with the manufacturers symbol and year of manufacture
ACCURACY: 3-10round groups not to exceed 2.00 inch mean radius maximum average at 200 yards
INSTRUMENTAL VELOCITY: 3165 +/- 40 FPS (78 feet from muzzle) using a 5.56 test barrel, 20 inches long
ENERGY: 1223 Ft-Lbs. at 78’
CHAMBER PRESSURE: Piezotronic maximum average per 10 rounds - 55000 PSI in 5.56 test barrel (case mouth location)
BULLET PULL: Minimum individual 35 lbs.
PROPELLANT DETECTION: 100% mechanical/electronic detection of propellant levels within the cartridge
VISUAL INSPECTION: 100% visual inspection of finished cartridges prior to packaging
WARNING: For use in standard 5.56 mm chambers. Do not use in non-standard 5.56 chambers.
PACKAGING: Bulk.

title: For Sale:  * RARE * Wilkinson Terry 9mm Tactical Entry Carbine * uzi * 9 mm
postcontent:
Listed here is a rare piece of firearm history that dates from the 1970’s and 1980’s. This is the Wilkinson Arms Terry 9mm Carbine. Based on an original design from J&R Engineering called the M68, this was a limited production run from a Mom & Pop style firearm manufacturer that placed too much emphasis on perfection and quality that subsequently put them out of business.

The Terry carbine is chambered in 9mm and is a pistol caliber carbine. Although it has the legal barrel length of 16in, several inches of the barrel reside in the receiver to give an extremely compact tactical package. The end of the barrel features a muzzle brake enclosed by a flash suppressor cone. As you can see from the pictures, the barrel removed from the receiver by simply unscrewing a washer which then breaks the gun down into an extremely small and concealable package.

This carbine was designed as a tactical entry carbine for use by law enforcement and SWAT teams. This gun takes 32 round magazines and feeds in the same manor of an Uzi. This gun will out-shoot an UZI all day long with accuracy and reliability. The quality of manufacturing and materials put the cheaply stamped UZI to shame. This thing functions as solidly as a bank vault! Essentially, this is the American Uzi that never made it mainstream. The upper part of the receiver is formed so that a simple claw scope mount can be mounted and optics utilized. I can personally attest that of the 3 times I have shot this rifle, I had no problem hitting a man size metal target from 100-150yrds. This carbine is an absolute joy to shoot and the 9mm ammo is not only affordable, it can be shot at any gun range to boot!

Wilkinson Arms also manufactured a much more common variant of this gun in pistol form known as the Linda. This particular example is in excellent condition and comes with 3 32 round magazines.

The stock is in BEAUTIFUL shape and the entire rifle looks great and functions fantastically.
I had plans to keep this locked in the safe but other projects force me to sell. Buyer is responsible to make sure they are legally able to purchase and own this weapon. A Washingtong State drivers license or CCL will be needed for my records only for the bill of sale. Please feel free to call or text with any questions. REDACTED
May take partial trade plus cash, let me know what you have.
